    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available for the discerning enthusiast is this 1995 Mazda RX-7, a masterpiece of 50:50 weight distribution and lightweight engineering. Powered by the legendary 13B-REW rotary engine, the sequential twin-turbocharger system delivers a linear torque curve and crisp throttle response. This example features a healthy compression profile and an upgraded aluminum radiator to manage thermal loads\u2014a critical preventative measure for the FD platform. The chassis remains taut, utilizing its four-wheel double-wishbone suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential for exceptional turn-in and lateral grip. While the exterior shows minor patina consistent with a well-loved driver\u2019s car, the mechanical vitals are robust, including a smooth-shifting 5-speed manual transmission and firm brake modulation. A true analog experience for those who appreciate technical purity.",
